description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated pharmacist with experience in cancer services to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Singleton Hospital is a Cancer Centre providing services to the population of South West Wales. The Cancer Centre includes a Radiotherapy Department, Oncology and Haematology chemotherapy day units and a dedicated Oncology/Haematology ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will lead on managing the pharmacy service provided for Womens cancer at Singleton, and will include working with the multi-disciplinary team at the Cancer Centre, managing pharmacist-led clinics lists, and leading on the implementation of newly approved NICE/AWMSG drugs in Womens Cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate take an active role in identifying and implementing Cost and/or Service Improvement Programmes, and will be responsible for producing and interpreting drug expenditure reports for Womens Cancer to inform the Cancer Services directorate. The post holder also will be expected to deliver education, training and development session to pharmacy providing pharmacy services to cancer clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameStuart John EvansJob titleClinical Effectiveness and Cancer PharmacistEmail addressstuartjohn.j.evans@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01792 285443&lt;/p&gt;
